 114:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/CMSIS_RTOS_V2/cmsis_os2.c ****   heap regions are already defined and vPortDefineHeapRegions is called in application.
 115:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/CMSIS_RTOS_V2/cmsis_os2.c **** 
 116:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/CMSIS_RTOS_V2/cmsis_os2.c ****   Otherwise vPortDefineHeapRegions will be called by osKernelInitialize using
 117:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/CMSIS_RTOS_V2/cmsis_os2.c ****   definition configHEAP_5_REGIONS as parameter. Overriding configHEAP_5_REGIONS
 118:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/CMSIS_RTOS_V2/cmsis_os2.c ****   is possible by defining it globally or in FreeRTOSConfig.h.
 119:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/CMSIS_RTOS_V2/cmsis_os2.c **** */
 120:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/CMSIS_RTOS_V2/cmsis_os2.c **** #if defined(USE_FreeRTOS_HEAP_5)
 121:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/CMSIS_RTOS_V2/cmsis_os2.c **** #if (configAPPLICATION_ALLOCATED_HEAP == 0)
